(define "NatalRules" 
 (rules "Natal Seas - Pods Rules
The pieces are called pods. Orca (Black with a white spot) plays first. Humpback (Grey) plays Second

The goal is territorial - To win, confine the opponents Pods to less than half the board.

Terminology
-- a player has 'influence' at a space surrounded by more friendly pods than other pods.
-- a 'dive' is the movement of a pod to an adjacent empty space.
-- To 'migrate' is to send a pod on a successive series of dives.

Dives have two restrictions:
- There must be a pod of either player that is adjacent, both to where the dive starts, and also to where it ends.
- The destination of the dive must not be under Enemy influence.

Play:
To start, Orca and Humpback in turn place a pod on any space except the center. Then regular turns continue in alternation.

On your turn do either (1) or (2):
Place a pod onto a space where you already have influence.
Migrate a pod.

Note: With multiple players you choose one player to skirt and only consider that player's influence. The other players' pieces block movement, but have no influence. 

Game End (2 player)
You win the game when you can show that your opponent can never reach more than half the board.

Natal Seas Tactics:
Create territory by completely surrounding it with solid and/or diagonal walls of pods, or with pairs of pods next to an edge.

Your territory also includes adjacent pairs of spaces if each of the pair has at least 3 friendly pods around it. 

Each piece played also counts as your territory.

But it is also important to move into regions that your opponent is trying to wall off. This is especially important early in the game. You can afford to build up a few pieces first, if you don't wait to long, or have good control over an important area of the board.
"
))

(define "WhalePieces"
    (board Background fillColour:(colour 190 228 255) edgeColour:(colour 170 160 140) scale:1.3)
    (piece Foreground state:1 image:"disc.svg" fillColour:(colour 190 228 255 150) edgeColour:(colour 190 228 255 150) scale:.8)
)

(define "HalfSurroundedSitesOf"
 (forEach
  (sites Around (sites Occupied by:All) <Board:dir>)
  if:(=
   ("NeighborCountAt" (site))
   (* 2 (count Pieces of:#1 in:(sites Around (site) <Board:dir>)))
)))


(define "PlayerInfluencedSites"
 (difference
  ("SitesInfluenceOfFor" #2 #1) 
  (union
   ("NaturalTerritoryOf" #1)
   ("HalfSurroundedSitesOf" #1)
))) 


(metadata
 (info 
  {
    
   (description "Pods is a stand-alone script variant of Natal Seas.
   
The script has now been updated to calculate permanent territory and end the game promptly, instead of playing it out until there are no moves left..  The AI uses heuristics based on the heavy calculations needed to determine the game ending. Use the A/B ai setting and make sure that the time is sufficient to complete at least the first level throughout the game.
 The heuristics are detailed enough to guide play reasonably with just 1 or 2 severch levels - but therefore they do miss long-range strategy.
"
   )
   ("NatalRules")
   (version "1.3.12")
   (classification "board/space/blocking")
   (author "Dale W. Walton")   
   (credit "Dale W. Walton")
   (date "2024-02-25")
  }
 )

 (graphics 
  {
    (board Style Graph)
    (board Colour InnerEdges (colour 62 72 55 150))
    (board Colour OuterEdges (colour 62 72 55 150))
    (board Colour InnerVertices (colour LightGrey)) // (colour 170 160 140))
    (board Colour OuterVertices (colour LightGrey)) // (colour 170 160 140))
    (board StyleThickness InnerVertices 1.35)
    (board StyleThickness OuterVertices 1.35)
    (board StyleThickness OuterEdges .15)
    (board StyleThickness InnerEdges .15)
    (board Background fillColour:(colour HumanLight) edgeColour:(colour 170 160 140) scale:1.3)
    (show Edges Diagonal <Board:diag> (colour 62 72 55))
    (player Colour P2 (colour Grey))
    (player Colour P1 (colour White)) 
    ("WhalePieces")
    (piece Scale "Disc" 0.8)
    <Heuristics:isVisible>
  }
 )
 (ai
  (bestAgent "Alpha-Beta")
  (heuristics
   {
    (score weight:20) //to prevent the abandonment of large scoring regions
   }
 )) 
)

(define "HeuristicScoreOf" // Note: converges to 2 * Territory when board is full
 (+ 
  (* 3 (count Pieces of:#1))
  (+
   (results
    from:(union
     (sites Empty) 
     (intersection
      (sites State 1) 
      (sites Occupied by:(player #1))
    ))
    to:(sites Around (from) <Board:dir> if:(= #1 (who at:(to))) includeSelf:True)
    (if (= (to) (from)) 1 2)
))))

